Programme Summary
In conjunction with Workforce Singapore, NTU offer traineeships to support the SGUnited Traineeships Programme. The Traineeships are part of NTU's efforts to create relevant and meaningful traineeship opportunities for our nation’s new graduates entering the workforce during this difficult time.

About School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering
NTU School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE) is now one of the top-ranked schools in the world, ranked 6th worldwide in the QS University Rankings by Subject 2019 (Electrical and Electronic Engineering). NTU EEE is also the first and only Asian School in the Top 20 (ranked 12th) for the Shanghai Ranking's Global Ranking of Academic Subjects 2019 - Electrical &amp; Electronic Engineering.

Job Descriptions:

  Carry out in-situ measurement and recording at construction sites
  Analyze and organize the recorded data
  Assist on setting up demos in lab and in-situ


Requirements:

  Able to analyze acoustic data, extract acoustic features and classify signals
  Able to do basic programming and building some interfacing hardware


